headline: Wall Street Weighs Up Odds of an Interest-Rate Cut
summary: The big question on investors' minds this morning: Will today’s inflation report push the Federal Reserve to cut interest rates this fall?  The report shows “inflation is under control, even if not quite at target,” said Daniel Siluk of Janus Henderson Investors.  The Fed, which tends to focus on a gauge known as PCE, targets a 2% inflation rate.

headline: Inflation Data Boosts Rate-Cut Bets
summary: Traders think the new inflation data makes a Federal Reserve interest-rate cut next month even more of a sure thing.    Futures pricing Tuesday morning suggested traders saw a 91% chance that the Fed will cut rates at its next meeting, according to CME Group data, up from 86% Monday.
